  "unmapped_findings": [
    "Fracture surface of 15Mn5Ni alloy specimen showed quasi-cleavage fracture with crack initiation-controlled failure, unlike dimple morphology in 28Mn0Ni and 28Mn5Ni.",
    "Dislocation-twin interaction mechanisms were noticed in fully recrystallized austenite leading to enhanced strain hardening and ductility.",
    "Planar slip activity and dynamic slip band refinement were observed in fully recrystallized austenite.",
    "B2 stringers underwent concurrent deformation with austenite grains, resulting in significant reduction in average thickness from ~8 um to ~2 um and fragmentation.",
    "Ni addition in lower Mn LDS (15Mn5Ni) reduced the processing temperature window of the alloy in two-phase region.",
    "15Mn5Ni alloy exhibited cracking beyond 50% cold reduction, hence further reduction was not carried out."
  ]
